  "show": {
    "date": "1985-08-16",
    "comments": [
      "Lister's comment: \"This one was a good show that represents a lot of what I loved about the Friday Rock Show. The range of music is wide, from prog rock like Pendragon and Marillion to early extreme metal like Venom, not to mention Battalion of Saints, a heavy punk band. Some of the tracks came from singles or albums only available on import, while others were more mainstream releases. Much of the show is taken up by contemporary releases while The Lie Back and Enjoy It selection is made up of solid classics and the Monsters of Rock sweep included some classic tracks too.\""
    ]
  },
